tes slurred fourth\ndyads over C#5 and A5 chords, as well as a heavy, \nspace-conscious riff of dyads\n(E5-D5-G5-D5-E5) over a low E pedal. The chorus \nconcludes with two measures of B5\npounded out in quarter-note rhythm.\n\n\nINTRO (0:11)\n\n       Dum,  dum,_ dum, hon-ey  what have you _ done?\n 1\n\nE|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nB|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nG|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nD|------------------9----------|-9------------9--------\nA|------------------7----------|-7------------7--------\nE|-----------------------------|-----------------------\n\n    Dum,   dum,_ dum it's the  sound of my   gun.\n 3\n\nE|----------------------------|------------------------\nB|----------------------------|------------------------\nG|----------------------------|------------------------\nD|9---------------9-----------|-9-------------9--------\nA|7---------------7-----------|-7-------------7--------\nE|----------------------------|------------------------\n\n       Dum,   dum,_ dum,hon-ey what have you_ done?\n 5\n\nE|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nB|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nG|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nD|---9---------------9---------|-9----------9----------\nA|---7---------------7---------|-7----------7----------\nE|-----------------------------|-----------------------\n\nE|-----| \nB|-----| \nG|-----| \nD|9----| \nA|7----| \nE|-----| \n\n    Dum,   dum,_ dum it's the sound,  it's the sound.\n 7\n\nE|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nB|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nG|-----------------------------|-----------------------\nD|9---------------9------------|-9---------------9-----\nA|7---------------7------------|-7---------------7-----\nE|-----------------------------|-----------------------\n\n       Nyah,    nyah,     nyah.                        \n      Nyah,    n